	<text>
		<pb n="2" facs="EHRI-DR-19391021_EN_02.jpg"/>
		<body>
			<p><!--Irving N. Linnell, Forced Departure from Moravska-Ostrava of Male Jews, Prag, 21.10.1939, S. 2: Records of the Department of State relating to internal affairs of Czechoslovakia 1910-1944, Washington 1982 (Mikrofilm-Edition): Dokument 860F.4016/83--></p>
			<p>It would seem, from all indications, that the intent is to obtain a large group of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1057" type="subject">workers</term> for use in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName>. What this use is seems to be problematical, but
				it may well be to prepare a place for the permanent <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1173" type="subject"
					>settlement</term> of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">families</term>, etc.,
				of these <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term>. It would seem that this
				movement may well be part of a larger movement of populations which the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1032" type="subject">German authorities</term> are carrying out, including
				the bringing back of <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_germans">German</term><term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">families</term> from the Baltic States, <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2017370/russian-federation.html">Russia</placeName>, and those parts of <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName> recently occupied by <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2017370/russian-federation.html">Russia</placeName>. There are many <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-852" type="subject">rumors</term>, but to date unverified, that the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1032" type="subject">German authorities</term> intend to bring into <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/admindistricts-212">Bohemia and Moravia</term> many of the <term
					ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> who are being <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-623" type="subject">evacuated</term> from others sections of <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/6255148/europe.html">Europe</placeName>, including some of those who are leaving the country near the
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">German</placeName>-<placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3017382/republic-of-france.html">Frenche</placeName>French war zone. If these <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-852" type="subject">rumors</term> are warranted, it may well be the plan
				to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-575" type="subject">replace </term>some of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jewish populations</term> in <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/admin/keywords/terezin-places-place-iti-64">Bohemia and Moravia</placeName> by <term
					ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_germans">German</term> populations.</p>
